#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Per-joint ROS 2 bridge node for Ingenia Everest CANopen drives.

Mirrors the wire protocol of copley_bridge / epos2_j3_bridge so the
existing orchestrator can drive a mixed-vendor arm without caring
which vendor is behind a given joint:

  Services:
    /ingenia/jN/clear_fault          (std_srvs/Trigger)
    /ingenia/jN/arm_ipm              (std_srvs/Trigger)
    /ingenia/jN/disarm_ipm           (std_srvs/Trigger)
    /ingenia/jN/move_absolute_timed  (epos2_bridge_interfaces/MoveAbsoluteTimed)

  Subscriptions:
    /ingenia/jN/reduced_traj         (Float64MultiArray, [q,v,dt,...])

  Publications:
    /joint_states                    (sensor_msgs/JointState)
    /ingenia/jN/fault                (std_msgs/Bool)

  Action server:
    /jN_position_controller/follow_joint_trajectory

PDO layout assumed (configure with apply_ingenia_pdo_remap_one.sh):
  RPDO1  ->  0x2181 (pos i32) + 0x2183 (time u16)
  RPDO2  ->  0x6040 ctrlword (16) + 0x6060 mode (8)
  RPDO3  ->  0x2182 (vel f32) + 0x2184 (integrity-commit u16)
  TPDO1  ->  0x2185 (record status u16) + 0x6041 statusword (16) + 0x6061 mode (8)
  TPDO2  ->  0x6064 position actual (32) + 0x606C velocity actual (32, counts/sec)
"""

